How to install vue3

1. download nodejs - nodejs.org
2. create a folder (a parent folder)
3. open vscode and the folder you just created
4. open terminal (default terminal not bash)
5. type npm install -g @vue/cli (to check node version: node -v)
6. type vue create PROJECT_NAME
7. press enter and pick vue3 not vue2
*****
Now, you should browse to the sub-folder you just created in procedure no.5
(the actual project folder)
8. type npm run serve
9. ctrl+click http://localhost:8080/ to view your work locally

***install extensions: vetur, vue 3 snippets
***under src, App.vue is the main page, sub pages go under components. You should link sub pages to main vue page.
*** < + tab key auto-completes template (vetur)

***************************************
When creating another project, use console and type vue create PROJECT_NAME
Typing npm install -g @vue/cli under the parent folder is done only once in the beginning.
But of course, if you create another parent folder to hold project folders, you should start from npm install -g @vue/cli
***************************************
